----- demo.font-changes

This text is in the default font. (Obviously). $[nl=2]

$[font=alt] This text, however, is in the alternative font. $$ $[nl=2]

Please note that newlines are sensitive to font changes, meaning you
will want to separate out your \$$ and \$[nl=...] directives
for the best effect.

----- demo.frame-counters

#[mark-frame-counter=0] This text appears first. #[mark-frame-counter=1] $[nl=1]
#[set-frame-counter=200] This text appears after a while. $[nl=1]
#[restore-frame-counter=0] This text appears first as well! $[nl=1]
#[restore-frame-counter=1] This text appears second, kinda.


----- demo.dialogue

This is an example of using the "dialogue" macro. $[nl=2]

%dl(SOMEBODY)% Wow! This is auto-indented! $$ $[nl=2]

Note that you must manually pop with \$$ at the end of your dialogue.